article_title: Marine Harvest Seeks to Garner Interest From U.S. Investors
article_text:
OSLO—The world's biggest salmon farmer, Norway's Marine Harvest, is looking to rally U.S. investors around the aquaculture sector's role in meeting a substantial portion of the world's growing need for food through increased fish production.

Marine Harvest will be listed on the New York Stock Exchange Tuesday, joining U.S.-listed protein companies that may be more familiar to American investors, including Tyson Foods Inc. and...
